Tarn Taran district is one of the districts in the Majha region of Punjab, India. The main cities are Tarn Taran Sahib and Patti. The City of Taran Taran is a holy place for Sikhs.
&nbsp;
Tarn Taran district was formed in 2006 from Amritsar District. The declaration to this effect

Amritsar, historically also known as Rāmdāspur and colloquially as Ambarsar, is a city in northwestern India which is the administrative headquarters of the Amritsar district and is located in the Majha region of the Indian state of Punjab.
